==Slovak==
=== Personal Pronoun ===
'''sa''' ''or'' '''seba'''

Replaces the [[accusative]] of any personal pronoun whenever the [[object]] is of the same [[person]] as the [[subject]]. Typically can be translated as the corresponding version of ''oneself'':
:'''vidím sa v zrkadle'''&mdash;''I see myself in the mirror

=== Reflexive Pronon ===
'''sa'''

Bound with certain verbs, similar to the Italian [[si#Italian|si]], but only when an [[accusative]] is appropriate. The pronoun is a part of the verb. For example, '''modliť sa'''&mdash;''to pray''. There is no '''modliť''' in Slovak without the '''sa'''.

Not to be confused with '''[[si#Slovak|si]]''', which is a [[dative]] reflexive pronoun.